\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Air temps can drop so rapidly in the first few centimeters above the soil that long legs can be an advantage for a smal animal. Man y desert lizards stretch out their ligs full length and lift their bodies as high as they can. Ground hugging desert creatures live in a world very different to our experience at the higher altitudes of human existence.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Shimmer/atmospheric boil - bubbles of heat rising in the cool air causing objects to ripple at a distane. Larger versions, high in the air, are called thermals. Hawk wheeling in the sky. }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Rising air carries scent of decaying flesh.}
