\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Desert soils are unusual. They vary tremendously in texture; many are sandy and gravelly, while others contain layrs of sticky clay, or even rock-hard, white limy layers. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85 in themore arid parts, surfaces of some soils are covered by a ayer of small stones that can be as tighty interlocked as a roman mosaic, and are coated with dark, shiny rock varnish. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Gravelly or stony aluvial fans that spil out of mountain drainages into adjacent basins cover much of the face of the sonoran desert.  The sediments that get transported are finer - snads, silts, clays. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Many sois of the piedmonts and basin floors start out as deposits of gravelly or stony lluvium tht have fairly uniform chracteristics throughout. With the passage of time, however, pronounced horizontal layers called}{\f1\fs24\b1\i0  soil horizons}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  develop. You can often aisliy see these horizons in oder, well-developed sois because they differ from one nother in color. }
